CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 26, 1945, pg. 3, reads: "Glad to be Home - These two Naval men, James Brooks, cook 3/c (left), and Morris Micheaux, steward 3/c, are home, after completing two years of service in the South Pacific.  Both of them have received Presidential citation medals. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: James Brooks and Morris Micheaux wearing dark U. S. Navy uniforms with Petty Officer, third class, Cook patches on sleeves, posed in front of light colored background, in Harris Studio
